snippet: In the worst violence in at least a month for the continuing protest movement in Ukraine, men in masks clashed with the police over new laws cracking down on public assembly.
abstract: Large rally in Kiev, Ukraine, called in part to protest a new set of laws cracking down on public demonstrations, turns violent when protestors attack police with sticks and throw firecrackers and cobblestones at them; violence, worst in month, signals deepening of country's political crisis.

byline.contributor: Oksana Lyachynska contributed reporting from Kiev, Ukraine.

lead_paragraph: In the worst violence in at least a month for the continuing protest movement in Ukraine, men in masks clashed with the police over new laws cracking down on public assembly.

headline.main: In Ukraine Protests Over New Laws, Sticks and Stones Are Met With Tear Gas
headline.print_headline: In Ukraine Protests Over New Laws, Sticks and Stones Are Met With Tear Gas
